<paragraph blockId="12.[151,467,1222,1249]" box="[151,467,1222,1249]" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,467,1222,1249]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="12" pageNumber="41" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="Dirsh, 1958" authorityName="Dirsh" authorityYear="1958" box="[151,467,1222,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Xiphoceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,467,1222,1249]" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,316,1222,1249]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">Xiphoceriana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dirsh" box="[323,467,1222,1248]" pageId="12" pageNumber="41" pagination="299 - 400" refId="ref11934" refString="Dirsh V. M. (1958) Revision of the group Portheti (Orthoptera: Acridoidea). Eos, Revista espanola de Entomologia, 34, 299 - 400" type="journal article" year="1958">Dirsh, 1958</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1293,1501]" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Dirsh" box="[307,452,1293,1320]" pageId="12" pageNumber="41" pagination="299 - 400" refId="ref11934" refString="Dirsh V. M. (1958) Revision of the group Portheti (Orthoptera: Acridoidea). Eos, Revista espanola de Entomologia, 34, 299 - 400" type="journal article" year="1958">Dirsh (1958)</bibRefCitation>
the main differences of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dirsh" authorityYear="1958" box="[846,998,1294,1320]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Xiphoceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[846,998,1294,1320]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">Xiphoceriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dirsh" authorityYear="1958" box="[1070,1221,1294,1320]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Lobosceliana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1070,1221,1294,1320]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">Lobosceliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the single-segmented medial part of antenna, the strongly toothed and slightly incurved upper margin of the hind femur and the projecting posterior margin of the epiphallus. However, the medial part of the antenna in some specimens may be divided in two and the slightly incurved upper margin of hind femora may be present in some specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dirsh" authorityYear="1958" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Lobosceliana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">Lobosceliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Overall, as will be discussed below, it is difficult to separate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dirsh" authorityYear="1958" box="[933,1085,1438,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Xiphoceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[933,1085,1438,1464]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">Xiphoceriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dirsh" authorityYear="1958" box="[1155,1306,1438,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Lobosceliana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1155,1306,1438,1464]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">Lobosceliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for certain, and they may be synonyms.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
